  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Saving Lives in Niger, Mali &amp; Sahel Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After years of unpredictable rains and poor harvests, along with existing intense poverty, 6 million people in the Sahel Region face significant food shortages this year. The UN and Government of Niger have both declared this situation a serious crisis. Mercy Corps teams work in the most at-risk areas, and have expanded programs to Mali, where 3.5 million experience chronic hunger. We help communities deal with effects of drought, soaring food prices, malnutrition and low food levels.</narrative>
  </description>
